Driver, who was gerast with 210 km / h and hot drink between the legs, receives £1,000 fine
A motorist was imposed a fine of £1,000, because he was up to 210 km / h and a hot drink between his legs.
Andrew Howie, 35, from Tiptree, Essex, was stopped on May 27, with his Mercedes Benz on the A120 in Braintree.
After the police had stopped him, they discovered the beverage cup between his legs.
Before the District Court Colchester Howie pled guilty to be driven without the necessary care and attention.
He received seven points and a six-month ban.
Howie was also sentenced to pay costs of £90 and a victim surcharge of £100.
